Yikes. Did I step on a Hornets nest or what. Arthur, your last post, above, was wonderful. Yes, I am guilty of hiding behind my clinical shield, and will do that no longer. I can not walk in your shoes, but I can try and understand your pain, and that of the others, WITHOUT clinical judgement and analysis. I will try.  That is the best I can offer.<br><br>
SW: I understand your post and thank your for the patience you are giving me to understand what it is like on your side of the table. I am trying, really, to do that.<br><br>
Cook: Ah, why do I try. It seems like a week ago we almost agreed on something, now you are back to throwing stones at me.What purpose does it serve for you to insult me with such stupid questions as your posted?  Why are you so threatened by me and my presence?  I am not a commie, remember? If you are such a big and brave war hero, then you should be able answer my innocent questions without hatred. I asked simple questions and you come down on me with big gun replies. Spatism and the like. Total over-reaction. Makes me wonder why? Makes me wonder why and what is under your macho bullshit. But, you know, I don't care, so lets drop that line of inquiry.  Remember, we fish seperate sides of the lake.<br><br>
I still work with VN Vets, and everything I learn here I can use to help speed up their healing.  Telling them I am a no good commie certainly won't be a help in counseling.<br><br>
As Arthur wrote above, I won't ever see a clinical picture of PTSD here cause emotions rule. That must also be applied to Cook. Given the anger, unwanted and unneeded, that he has erruped with, I think he too must be on the PTSD roll call. I guess he is too manly to admit it.  So he defers, detracts, reflects, and ducks anything that comes close.<br><br>
SW, Arthur, Thank you for your well spoken replies to my innocent questions. Cook, I urge you to read and re read your post, and ask yourself why the rage? (and leave my kids out of this, unless you really want to piss me off, jarhead).<br><br>

